Location: a. Descent Trail Area > Ralph Stover State Park (High Rocks) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A roof problem on the detached outcrop at the top of the descent trail.  Pull the roof w/o using cheater blocks.  Often top roped due to the bad landing.

Location: b. Practice Face > Ralph Stover State Park (High Rocks) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Pull the overhang onto an awkward, sloping ledge.

Location: b. Practice Face > Ralph Stover State Park (High Rocks) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Begin at the Practice Chimney and climb down and right below an overhanging bulge.  Continue right just above the ground until you reach the grungy section at the Weeping Wall.

Location: b. Practice Face > Ralph Stover State Park (High Rocks) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Reach up for the jug and climb the arete for 5 feet to a stance.  Escape left.  Use only the overhanging arete for feet.

Location: c. Neolithic Wall > Ralph Stover State Park (High Rocks) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the blank face betwen two cracks to a small ledge at 13 feet.The cracks and adjacent holds are off route.

Location: Meeker > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: An enjoyable easy route, a good warmup for the harder routes in the area. Sit start on a left sloping edge and move directly up right of the arete created with the alcove. Some fun movements that will loosen the joints. Assume theÂ alcove and the crack above it are off.

Location: Meeker > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start sitting on the boulder.  Squeeze the overhanging prow to the top.

Location: Meeker > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start as low as possible.  Squeeze the overhanging prow to the top.

Location: V2 Boulder > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the face to the slopey top out up and left.

Location: Patoggan Run > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Looking directly atPatoggan Run, start in the rounded dihedral near the left arete with a good edge on the arete. Smear up into the dihedral and traverse right to joinPattogan Run.

Location: Patoggan Run > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the blunt, slabby arete to the right of the V6 slab.

Location: Patoggan Run > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the steep slab.

Location: Patoggan Run > Meeker Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: If you are looking directly atPatoggan Run, it's the right side of the boulder.Start on the left side of the face with a good low foothold, just right of a dead tree stalk. Traverse right along the face with good footholds in the low crack. Link intoPaddle Prowat the right arete.

Location: Bubblegum > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: The standard warmup problem for the area, start on two sidepulls and follow big holds to the finish.

Location: Bubblegum > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on low undercling with a good left foot and move up into Bubblegum Face

Location: Bubblegum > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Same SDS as Bubblegum. Go to first good horizontal and straight up from there to a crimp and then huge jug. Top out.

Location: Bubblegum > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on two jugs down low and work left to a good horizontal then up to a diagonal crimp, move right to a gaston (easier) or bring the right hand up to a good jug and top out.

Location: Bubblegum > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb out the cave left of Bubblegum.  Strenuous topout with high dab potential.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on jug and traverse right across boulder on good crimp rail with a few small feet

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on a jug on the right of the boulder and traverse left on the lip using small edges, turn the corner of the boulder and top out.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the overhanging crack to the juggy rail then over the top of the overhang.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start on a good sidepull and sloping hold.  Move up to a small crimp in the middle of the face and to a weird pocket/shallow sidepull.  Make a big move up to a good edge, and then to a pinch and top out.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climbs the prow. Start down in the pit, slightly around the corner on a horizontal crack. Trend leftwards out around the prow then straight up.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Between Gumball (L) and Black Angus (R). Use left arete and the seam of Black Angus. WIDE arms.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This climb is prominent, inspiring, and a little bit dicey, with great moves!To start it, step off the big platform onto the start holds (low left hand slopey sidepull, right hand incut but small crimp) above a very dangerous gap in the platform. Climb up through a small horn and a gaston to a jug near the tree, then a fairly moderate topout.Important: have an attentive spotter ready to push you *away* from the boulder onto the pads, to avoid the pit (maybe throw a pad down in the pit anyway in case you slide down). I felt fairly safe on it because you are pushing away from the pit to move upward, but the feet are very bad so a slip is possible.

Location: Black Angus Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with a large sidepull. Climb up past a gaston, a pinch, a two finger slot, and finally the thin seam on the slab.

Location: Savage Hand Orgy > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Fun sit-down-start and make a huge move or dyno to an obvious sloper and top out above

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start at the right side of the face and traverse the lip.  Top out around the left arete.

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with incut holds on the left. Climb the sloping lip. Great warm up!Beta Video

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the right side of the slab.

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on edges, move up and right to a long crimp rail then up to a good U-shaped hold one foot below the lip.

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on small edges and stemming in a subtle corner, move up on small edges and top out.

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start at the big footholds, move up to opposing sidepulls and make a big move for the top.

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Crimpy face to the right of Over the Falls

Location: Over the Falls Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Not sure of the exact details... climbed this problem while on a trip to Haycock. Great arete problem if I recall correctly.

Location: Of Mice and Men Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Short and easy roof climb. Get as low as you can to SDS on good sidepulls/underclings, then fire out, up , and over on jugs. Not much to it, but it is one of the few easy roof climbs (nearly horizontal) to be found at Haycock.

Location: Of Mice and Men Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start on the right side of a fairly large boulder, with a rail and the prow for hands. Move up to a good jug, then continue trending left up the arete to top out.

Location: Of Mice and Men Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on underclings and move up left to a series of good sidepulls.

Location: Of Mice and Men Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: S.D.S. matched on a protruding hold down low. Use a couple incut sidepulls to reach a jug on the lip. Top-out directly above.

Location: Of Mice and Men Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS at the base of the blunt arete. Work up into underclings and then the seam above. Get your feet way up and make a huge reach to a good hold at the lip the boulder.

Location: Of Mice and Men Area > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with a jug on the prow. The right arete is off. Reach up to an edge, then to the terrible flat gaston sloper. Match it, and continue up edges on the left face.

Location: Southwest Boulder > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Stand start on jug and climb up jugs and good slopers to easy top out.

Location: Southwest Boulder > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS on two good crimps with a good left foot, stand and reach to good sloping edge and then up to another crimp.  Tricky top out.

Location: Southwest Boulder > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start.  Climb the face left of the arete without using the arete.

Location: Southwest Boulder > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS matched on jug and climb several small crimps to tenuous top out.

Location: Upper Hangar > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with high left on the left arete and a low right hand crimp. Move up and out to the left to top out.https://vimeo.com/64966772#t=3m57s

Location: Upper Hangar > Hangar 18 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start matched on a large jug in the center of the face and move up.vimeo.com/64966772#t=0m56s

Location: Nadja > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb straight up the large crack that turns into a finger crack halfway up the boulder.

Location: Nadja > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start climbing the large crack and follow the finger crack that trends left.

Location: Nadja > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Share the same start as Nadja. Step on just left of a small tree and follow the scoop up and right.

Location: Nadja > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start just left of the small tree and climb straight up the slab face on small crimps/seams and tricky feet.

Location: Mo Mangoes > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on a low edge and climb up to the sloping rail. Follow the sloping rail up and right and top out.Very mellow climb and very short.

Location: Mo Mangoes > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: One of the best v7's at Haycock. Definitely worth adventuring down the Caves Trail to find.This problem (along with the few variations and The Plum) is somewhat tucked away in a cave type formation.SDS on the hold that is continually chalked. Move right to the big undercling, then up the nice crimps on the face. Hit the arete and climb up and over.Word of caution, the bottom of this climb is always always wet.

Location: Mo Mangoes > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start the same as Mo Mangos, but instead of reaching up for the crimps on the face, continue right past the big undercling to another undercling and continue out to the crack. From here, climb up the crack and follow the arete.Dab potential on the boulder that is home to The Plum is very high on this one. Its quite scrunched.

Location: The Tooth > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on a curved crimp on the left and climb the face to the notch in the center.

Location: The Tooth > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the right arete of the Tooth Boulder.

Location: The Tooth > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start at the big prominent jug near the bottom of the arete. Climb the arete utilizing nice crimps to a solid top out.

Location: The Tooth > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Although unnamed, this is a pretty nice climb nonetheless. Starts on the same jug as Novocaine and traverse rightward, following the seam. Head for the notch in the top of the boulder.

Location: The Magi Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS on the right side of the roof on the arete. Work your way up and left across the face to a good crimp at the lip of the roof. Pull up from here and top out above.

Location: The Magi Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start under the roof on a good incut for your left hand. Using the below boulder as a kick plate, reach up to the good crimp at the lip of the roof. Pull up and over and top out directly above.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on jugs at the base of the huge crack. Climb straight up into the scoop on bomber holds.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Just to the left of Sumo Wrestler, climb the slab.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Brace yourself for perhaps the hardest v2 on the mountain. Being able to crimp v-hard will not automatically mean you will be able to power up this arete. Be prepared for a fun challenge deciphering this technical climb.Balance up the left side of the arete.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: stand start with a side pull for your right and an edge out left right above the chalked up slopey rail. get a high foot and carefully go for one of the crimps up high. top out straight above. a v3 variation exists starting from the slopey rail.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: S.D.S. climb the arete.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the right side of the obvious pit. Follow the rail leftward until you reach the large brick sized hold at the base of the sweeping feature. Stab up for the slopers at the lip and mantle over.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Its easy to locate this climb. This powerful yet somewhat short line has a really nice landing and is situated in the cave itself.Start with two high fingerlocks in the crack. Using bad foot smears, power up and exit left around the roof.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: If sharp crimps are your thing, be sure to give this one a go.Start on the very blunt arete on an obvious two handed crimp seam. Follow a few small crimps to a larger hold and then mantle up over the top.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with your left hand on a sloping rail and your right hand on a good crimp sidepull.  Get a high right foot and dyno for the slopey lip, then mantle over.  This problem was originally climbed at V5, using the right hand side pull and a small left hand crimp up high.  The crimp now appears to be broken off, making the dyno significantly longer and more difficult.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the ball. Start off with fist jams and trend rightward.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the jug on the right arete and follow the obvious line across the 45 degree wall. Reach the crack in the dihedral and continue up to a triangular jug. From here, jump off.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Starting on the big jug on the left arete, follow the long arete up the boulder.

Location: The Caves > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This is a rather tall boulder with a somewhat relatively flat landing. Climb the small seam that splits the face of this boulder.Start on a low pinch for your right and a pocket for your left.

Location: Top Rock/Caves Trail Split > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Excellent Haycock compression problem. Your right hand is low on a crimp under the overhang in the seam out right, your left on a good edge on the arete. Follow a few faint sloping edges on the seam and work you way out and up the arete.Careful not to dab on the ground boulder that is awkwardly placed directly under the start.

Location: Top Rock/Caves Trail Split > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start low on a sidepull and move up and right to finish.

Location: Three Seams > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Center and easiest of the Three Seams. Highball - commit to trusting feet and go.

Location: The Cracked Egg Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Follow the obvious crack up the left side of the boulder with a few locks, jams and jugs.

Location: The Cracked Egg Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Follow good flakes up the right side of the boulder to a thinner top out with good feet.

Location: The Cracked Egg Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Follow the thin line up the center of the boulder, do not use the crack to climbers left.

Location: White Top Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on a large undercling and high jug, get a high, good foot and follow the crack up using another jug and mantle over the lip.

Location: Bokow Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Eady slab problem. Stand start with two sidepulls, then to horizontal seam, then to top

Location: Bokow Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on two crimps left (sidepull/undercling) right (sidepull) at about chest height, get a high foot and slap your left hand up a rightward arching arete with bad feet.

Location: Bokow Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This is the boulder problem to the left and around the corner of Spined Micrathena. It probably has a name, so please fill it in if you know it.I started with my left hand at the lowest part of the arete and right hand on the obvious crimp. Start with a high foot and figure out how to get to the top. Rifle-esque

Location: Bokow Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on large undercling jug with high right foot, power and finesse you way up right to a good slot in the crack and continue to finesse up the crack with insecure feet.

Location: Bokow Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: "Start with a flat square hold and climb the prow up and right, finishing up in the dihedral on jugs to a nice top out. An amazing hanging prow feature."credit to Char for the description as this was taken from the Haycock Guidebook.

Location: The Rocking Chair > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: The right arete of the Rocking Chair boulder.Start with your right hand on the arete and your left hand in the notch near the lip. Pull on and trend rightwards up the prominent seam.

Location: The Rocking Chair > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start as for the rocking chair (squeezing with left hand in a notch and right hand on the arete), but go left through crimps to a bulbous sloper and top out straight up the left face.

Location: The Rocking Chair > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Interesting line (if its dry!)Start the same as Rocking Chair Direct. Sit start on the obvious low ledge on the left side of the boulder. Traverse low across the boulder using the prominent seam. Link in to Rocking Chair on the right arete and follow the seam and top out.

Location: The Rocking Chair > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Rocking Chair Direct is the left side of the Rocking Chair Boulder. Sit start on the obvious ledge that is low on the left side of the boulder. Work your way through some crimps and slots to the lip. Mantle over the lip and on to the slabby arete above. Top out on interesting seams, crimps, and slopers.

Location: Little Fluffy Clouds Area > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: short, but a good warmup for LFC;- sit start with a good left hand jug, low right hand compression sloper and feet smears- move your hands up into the good seams, eventually throwing right hand up to the amazing pinch jug. Get high feet, lockoff on that pinch, and balance your way up to a shallow seam. Easy top out after braving the less-than-decent fall potential.

Location: Little Fluffy Clouds Area > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A classic atypical Haycock line following a featured overhanging arete before pulling onto the face and the topout. Sit start utilizing an under cling with feet smearing on the face, climb the jugs and pinches with big moves and turn the lip with a small feet cut move before slapping up for the lip.

Location: Little Fluffy Clouds Area > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A few different options exist to crimp and slap your way up this one.SDS on the jug at the base of the arete. Using crimps and a sloper, make you way up to another jug about 3/4 of the way up the arete. An easier top out awaits.

Location: 3-Star > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Rating: 5.10- V1 WI2- M1-2 C1+ Easy Snow
Description: A Haycock classic highball finger crack.

Location: Dubeck > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Slap your way up the left arete of the Dubeck boulder.  Start low on a jug and go all the way to the top.

Location: Dubeck > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A typical Haycock diabase route - start using an undercling at the base of the lip and slap your way up the lip then right top out in the center of the boulder

Location: Dubeck > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Smack in the middle of the Dubeck boulder is this fun yet short problem.Start with a left hand on the lowest part of big sidepull and a right hand on sidepull down and right. Bump the left hand up and fire up and right to the arete. Follow the arete up.

Location: Amber Boulders > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start matched on a prominent edge on the right and climb up along the rail.

Location: Amber Boulders > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with a left side pull and a right rail. Find feet and fire for the top. Looks great but the feet are tricky, probably around V2.

Location: Amber Boulders > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the sloping rail up and right on the Amber Boulder, to a throw at the top.

Location: Bokow Area > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Stand start with a large foothold and slopers. Traverse left on crimps avoiding the lip until you reach the swooping arÃªte. Move up with jugs on the arÃªte and top out.

Location: Ice Cream Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start. Climb the sharp arete on the right in the photo

Location: Ice Cream Boulder > Caves Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with both hands on the undercling, climb the blunt arete on the left in the photo

Location: Top Rock > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A big boulder with an obvious west-facing line.

Location: Top Rock > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A low seam that starts wide on the right then thins up as you traverse left; top out above the 'TM' graffiti and don't dab on the Â blocks to the left. Depending on the beef of your hands, may feel harder than the grade.

Location: Top Rock > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: An arete line on the south edge of the boulder marked by 'VAPE' graffiti.

Location: Top Rock > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start up on the ramp with solid hand jams in the overhanging crack.  Climb over the roof as the crack gets thinner.  Might seem harder if you cant jam

Location: Top Rock > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb arete under Top Rock starting on large blocky rock. highball with pinches, pockets, slopers.

Location: Top Rock > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This is the big block just to the right of Iron Lion. Walk into the little corridor that houses Mighty Mouse.This route is the arete just next to the big tree. Start with both hands in the horizontal crack and climb the left arete. When the arete gets close to the tree, youre able to trend rightwards a bit on edges then up to the top.

Location: The Never Ending Biscuit > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Using the left arete and the dihedral, make some interesting moves moves up to the top.Although this problem is on the short side, its a v4 in the Top Rocks section worth checking out.

Location: Hematoma Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start in the crack in the back of the cave on the leftside of the little corridor that separates The Wookie and Witch Hazel. Start the same as The Wookie, in the crack at the back of the cave. Work your way up the crack and up on to the overhanging left face and reach around to the slab. Finish straight up.

Location: Hematoma Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Stand start on jugs and climb seam up the slab.

Location: Hematoma Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb into the cave and SDS on the prominent undercling. Work you way up the rail and the right arete until its possible to turn onto the face. Brace yourself for a somewhat tricky and elusive topout.Careful not to dab, this one gets a bit tight.

Location: Hematoma Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: In the cave on the right hand side of the small corridor lies the Wookie! Start in the crack at the back of the cave. Traverse leftward across the left overhanging face. Work your way through a heinous gaston and then out to the lip. Round the lip and make your way up the slab.

Location: The Watchtower Boulders > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: If lowball topouts is what youre searching for, then look no further. This odd shaped rock proves that even lowballs can be tricky.SDS on jug on right side and work your way out!

Location: The Watchtower Boulders > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This one doesnt usually see much action, so if youre trying to find it by looking for previously chalked holds, it might be impossible to find. Make sure to bring a brush too, just incase there is some moss buildup.SDS underneath the boulder on prominent crimps. Work your way out and up using compression and more crimps.

Location: The Broiler Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the wide vertical crack/flake system (second crack from the right) and top out in the gap. Great introduction to kinda-highball boulders; it's consistently easy movement the whole way up, with solid feet, the occasional hand jam, and a simple top out move. Recommend walking up the backside of the boulder first and locating the hidden jug on the top out.

Location: The Broiler Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the vertical crack on the right hand side of the downhill face of the boulder. Then follow the diagonal crack up and to the left, and top out in the gap. Walk around to the top and check to make sure the diagonal crack is clean before climbing it, this doesn't see much traffic.

Location: The Broiler Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Starting in the pit located between this boulder and the next one uphill, follow the diagonal crack to a slab below the bulge and top out directly above.

Location: Pyramid Boulder > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Low angle small hands size crack.

Location: El Patron > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the slopey arete to the top.

Location: El Patron > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with left hand at the bottom of the arete where it changes angles and right hand on the low sidepull crimp on the face. Climb up the arching arete with bad feet, small crimps, and amazing slopers. Be prepared to go all in on the top out. Instant classic!

Location: Trail Split Boulders > Top Rock Approach Boulders > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with opposing sidepulls on the right arÃªte. Climb the arÃªte and test your head game at the peak.

Location: Trail Split Boulders > Top Rock Approach Boulders > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS matched on the large undercling jug. Traverse the lip and top out at the peak. Gotta trust your toes on those smears.

Location: Trail Split Boulders > Top Rock Approach Boulders > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with left undercling and right sidepull. Climb the crimpy face to a large dish then make a shouldery move to the top.

Location: Trail Split Boulders > Top Rock Approach Boulders > Top Rock Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with opposing sidepulls on the right arÃªte. Traverse the face to gain the far left lip and finish up the left arÃªte. No knees!

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the overhanging face.  The boulder at the base is on.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS on a low rail with tiny feet, move up and left to a small vertical slot, hand foot match the rail, than follow jugs to top out. A bit of a one move wonder.Variation: Hugo Long - V4, Dyno from start hold to top out jug

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the underclings and climb the nose.  The boulder at the base is on.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the arete on small holds.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit Start to Cheese and Crackers, start on a poor crimp and side pull and bad feet, move up to the stand start holds.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the arete starting on slopey holds and top out.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the overhanging dihedral.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start under the roof and follow the crack out.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start to Garden spider party, start on a large crimp and feet close to the dirt.  Move up to the slopers and reach way up to more sloping holds and top out.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A one-move-wonder: dyno from the chalked up start holds of The Plug to the top.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start in the pit.  Climb small edges to the top.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Stand start.  Climb the overhanging prow.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the slab and traverse the boulder. Finish on the plug!

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit on the boulder to start.  Undercling up to pinches.

Location: Area 51 (uphill side) > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start.  Climb the overhanging prow.

Location: Chris' Acres > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the short hand crack in the dihedral.

Location: Chris' Acres > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start on the right side of the arete.  Climb the arete.

Location: Chris' Acres > Area 51 > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start at the low jug just right of the tree.  Climb straight up to the slopey top.

Location: Ninja Squirrel > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: thin crimps up face - arete is off

Location: Delicate Troll boulder > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the v-shaped slopers in the center of the boulder. Go up and right to a crimp rail, then fire out for the arete.

Location: Delicate Troll boulder > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: While Cooperazzi starts in the center on the obvious v-shaped jug, this variation starts on the left side with a small sloper on the arete for your left hand and the prominent low crimp for your right. Slap up the sloper and then lurch over to the v-shaped jug and then continue into Cooperazzi.

Location: Egg Roll > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Starts on an undercling under the roof. Move up and right and then top out. The boulder at the base is on for feet.

Location: The Perch > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: under overhanging roof start hold is a jug out to lip of roof, onto short face and straight up to top. Same start as Turkish Blend v5

Location: The Perch > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: under overhanging roof start hold is a jug out to lip of roof, onto short face via sloper, top out above

Location: The Perch > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: So many problems on such a little section of rock! Thats okay, theyre all good!This one starts underneath the small roof on the crack in the back. Starts the same as The Perch. Reach around to the low crimps on the face and head up to the slopers, the same as you would with The Perch. From here, traverse right into Light Shag and finish it up.

Location: The Perch > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS in the crack on the left side underneath the roof. Reach around the small roof to a crimp at the lip. Continue upward to slopers. From here, head up and left to a good flake. Top out above.

Location: Throwing Oranges at the Eskimos > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start from left facing flake, up face, past sloping dish

Location: Nightmare Arete > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Variation of Ulu (VB). Start on right of the wall with the Ulu crack and traverse left until you reach the crack. Finish on Ulu.Beta Vid (starts a few moves in)

Location: Nightmare Arete > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the beautiful face and arete with thought provoking and technical movement. This one will keep you on your toes.

Route: Jesus Calls For War Aka Nightmare Arete
Location: Nightmare Arete > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: overhanging arete

Location: Bootleg > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A very tricky and balancy arete problem! SDS on the left side of the arete. Work your way up the arete and top out at the peak.

Location: Rumble In The Jumble > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb down into the pit to start this boulder. Stand start with both hands on obvious start hold down and just left of the right arete. Make some crimpy moves up and left and then dyno out right to the jug crimp(crux). Work your way up and left along the lip of the boulder on small crimps until you can rock over onto the slab(also cruxy). Climb the easy but committing slab for 20ft. to the top of the boulder. A fall from the slab would be horrific and most likely injurious. What a gem!!

Location: Sitting Pretty > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with left hand on the cool, flat, triangular hold on the arete and right hand on the far right edge. The crux is getting established on the boulder and doing the first move up the arete. After that, reach up and right to the pretty, sloping lip. Work your feet up and do a move or two before going for the top. The mantle isn't hard but it is slightly awkward because of the lack of feet. Reachy.

Location: Grovelfest > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Inspired by Shadow's efforts!Start left hand on a good edge and right hand on a flaky side pull on the arete/crack. Use a high left foot smear and establish on the boulder. Using the arete/crack and crimps on the face, climb the slab. Everything right of the crack is off.

Location: Grovelfest > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with left hand on the arete and right hand underclinging the low lip. Climb the rounded boulder using the arete and crimps on the face until you can reach out right to the long incut crimp jug. Get your right foot up on the crimp jug and top out. The rock left of the arete/crack is off.

Location: Grovelfest > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS on the massive jug. Do a long move to crimps on the lip of the boulder. Top out.

Location: Grovelfest > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with right hand on the big, flat sidepull and left hand on any of the small, sharp crimps you choose. Figure out how to pull onto the boulder with terrible feet and make one hard move to the long crimp jug. Top out.

Location: Grovelfest > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with both hands in the seam and pull onto the boulder with terrible feet. Bust to the pancake slopers and drift out left to easier moves before topping out.

Location: Grovelfest > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with a left hand sloper on the lip of the boulder and a right hand crimp. Pull onto the boulder and do a move out left to a dishy crimp. Reach up right hand to a good high crimp with a thumb catch. Surmount the top of the boulder with bad feet and a lot of groveling. The name says it all.

Location: Air Out > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the right arete with a tricky start and a fun mantle in the middle of the problem on the protruding jug.

Location: Air Out > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with left hand on the arete and right hand on the small, smile crimp on the face. Make some moves to the horizontal crack in the middle of the face and then continue up the left arete with fun, techy moves.

Location: Air Out > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on Bill an Ted's. Once you get to the horizontal crack, traverse left and finish on Excellent Adventure.

Location: Air Out > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start matched on the long, slanted, sidepull undercling right of the left arete and the big foot. Reach up to the horizontal crack. Match the crack and go for the top. A fun eliminate. Watch out for the tree at your back.

Location: Team Effort > Gateway > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the fun slab with a vertical seam, dishy feet, a slopey arete feature, and cool crimps up high. This one will test your slab climbing skills.

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the prow being careful not to touch intrusively close tree, making way to top ledge across face and topping out to left.

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Tenuous layback up a flake

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with both hands on a good hold, go to the top slopers and top out.

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with a seam for your left and sidepull for your right.  Hike up your feet throw for the lip and top out.  Mind the tree, hence the name.

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: The leftmost line on the wall. Grovel up and over the buldge.

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start as for "Catching Flies", but traverse left into the start of "Funky Butt Love" utilizing a high heel and a right hand side-pull crimp. Slap around the arete to the seam, then slap to the lip and top out.Not sure if this has been climbed before or is described elsewhere, so feel free to update FA / grade.

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: No text - use the 'Improve This Page' link to add something useful!

Location: The Glass Wall > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit Start with crimps under the bulge, and feet on the detached rock. Climb up intoMain Squeeze.Be careful with the loose start hold.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start with hands on either side of the block, slap your way up the block to easier ground and follow the left angling crack to top out.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on good edges and climb 2 moves up before the holds stop, slap for the lip and find the good jug and top out.  The slopers to the right on the arete are off.  A V0 variation to this problem allows use of the arete.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: From Char Fetterolf's "Haycock Mountain Bouldering" guidebook:"Start with your choice of holds and climb the vertical seams.  Tough to get started."

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Teddy Bear Picnic is the leftward angling crack on the backside of the teddy bear area main boulder.  Begin the problem standing on the low boulder to gain a good finger lock and follow the crack using jams and small edges for feet to a slopey top out.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A technical climb, start on a sidepull and a good crimp under the perched boulder and move right on small edges.  Reach a good jam and position your feet higher to reach positive holds at the lip.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Traverse the slopey lip to top.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on theInto The Picnictraverse holds betweenTeddy Bear's PicnicandTit Tossand dyno up to a sharp edge below the lip, or skip it and go straight to the top.

Location: Teddy Bear Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A great link up of Tit Toss and Teddy Bear's Picnic. Start on Tit Toss and traverse left on good holds until you have to make a big reach to gain access to Teddy Bear's Picnic. Top out Teddy Bear's Picnic.

Location: Fun Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the subtle open book in the middle of the slab face.

Location: Fun Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Left side of the slab.

Location: Fun Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit down start on the overhanging side of the right arete.

Location: Fun Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the slopers above the bulge and mantle.

Location: Picnic Rock > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the middle of the face.

Location: Picnic Rock > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the arete.

Location: The Flaming Moe > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb up the arete on the left side of the boulder

Location: The Flaming Moe > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: climb the fairly tall crimpy face, without using arete.

Location: Deviled Egg > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Rather conditions dependent because of the slopers on this one!Start with a right hand crimp just left of center on the boulder and your right hand on a sloper dish. While the finish is a mere 3-4 feet away, find the ability to hump your way up the bulging arete. A bit deceiving but fun to figure out.

Location: Deviled Egg > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS squeezing where you can on the bottom of the egg shaped boulder. The kickplate underneath is on for feet. Find a way to pull on and up to the starting sloper for The Deviled Egg.

Location: The Amphitheater > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: The long traverse spans the boulder starting in a shallow dihedral on the far right side. The start isnt too well defined and you'll find yourself scratching your head looking for the best way to start this. Either way, start with low holds in the dihedral and work your way leftward. Using the prominent gaston and long seam, continue working leftwards and mantle on to the upper section of the boulder.

Location: The Amphitheater > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Time to hone in your dyno skills! This one has seen a bit of crumbling on the start hold so a community censuses on the grade is probably needed. Start with both hands on crimps in the seam. From here, dyno to the sloping lip. You'll trend right around lip and mantle up on to the face.

Location: Teddy Bear Satellite > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Offwidth crack, a tad bigger than most male fists.

Location: Teddy Bear Satellite > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Its easy to see that this line is always overlooked. The top will almost always have to be cleaned off and the same will have to be scrubbed from all the debris that built up from no one touching it for months (or years). Despite the fact that its unnamed and only a v3, its a rather fun line nonetheless.SDS in the pit. Left hand on a low but good crimp and right hand in the seam. Work your feet and follow the seam up to the lip. A few tension moves and good foot placements will see you hitting the lip and doing the fun topout. Just try to avoid the vegetation that has grown a few inches thick on top of this one!

Location: The Y Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the left arete on slopers and smears.

Location: The Y Boulder > Teddy Bear Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the right arete on slopers and smears. The pedestal in on.

Location: Chiba Boulder > The Hobo Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with your right hand on the horn and your left hand on a sidepull. Pull up to the slopy sidepull, match, and tension over to holds on the arete. Top out after reaching the big crimp rail up high.

Location: Hobo Boulder > The Hobo Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS on low jug and campus up to high jug or use a slopey intermediate.  Easy top out after reaching the high jug.

Location: Hobo Boulder > The Hobo Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Same start as Hobo but trend right and low on good holds to an easier top out

Location: Hobo Boulder > The Hobo Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on good jug and follow slopers straight up and top out in the depression at the top of the boulder.

Location: Hobo Boulder > The Hobo Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start In the crack and make a big move up to an edge in the horizontal crack. Traverse left to join and finish the same as Pipeline.

Location: Hobo Boulder > The Hobo Trail > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Was originally V10 but a small crimp broke and got better! Since, the problem hasn't seen enough ascents for everyone to agree on a grade.  Start on a good right hand and medium incut crimp.  Climb the overhang with side pulls, a decent crimp and a big pop to a sloping edge. Tricky top out.

Location: Proximity Infatuation Area > The Outliers > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This one is WAY out there. If youre up for some bushwacking, then this one is for you. Its well worth the effort to get out to this location.Start on the right side of the boulder and follow the prominent seam. Continue working leftward until its possible to hit the small crimp leading up the face. Hit the second seam and continue up the slabby top to the finish.

Location: 45 Degree Wall > The Outliers > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with a high right hand pinch and a left hand sidepull. Climb up and over the rounded arete.

Location: 45 Degree Wall > The Outliers > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: In the center of the wall is a L shaped hold at the top of a scar that runs up the middle. The L shaped hold is easy to spot, its formed by a right hand ledge and a left hand sidepull. Find feet and establish on this L shaped hold. Fire up for the lip. Trend rightwards across the lip and mantle on to the slab above. Careful on some of the higher portions of this slab, certain sections are fragile and prone to breaking.

Location: 45 Degree Wall > The Outliers > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: This is the lower start to the 45 Degree Wall. Start directly below the L shaped hold that defines the start of the 45 Degree Wall on two somewhat parallel edges/sidepulls. Work some tricky foot beta and find your way up in to the 45 Degree Wall start hold. Fire for the lip, trend right, and mantle on over.

Location: End of the Road Boulders > The Outliers > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with both hands low on the slab on good slanted crimps. Smear your way up and into the incredible tips crack. Using the crack and other finger jugs, move right and around the wide arete. With the use of bad feet, make some cruxy moves to the lip and jack your feet as high as you can. Top out on slopers.

Location: End of the Road Boulders > The Outliers > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with both hands on two small crimps next two one another high on the wall. **It helps to stand on a pad that is leaning on the slab landing to reach these holds. Pull onto the wall and make a move out right to the jug. Paste your feet on and go for the amazing "coaster" crimp at the lip. **The hold looks completely detached but it is very solid. Slap over the lip and top out on slopers.

Location: Eye > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Starting with a high lefthand sidepull on the face and a very low righthand sidepull on the arete, work your way up using the arete and the eye!

Location: Doe > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on giant ledge on the left side of the Doe Boulder face. Move left to sloping arete, up to right crimp--continue along the good side arete to finish top.

Location: Doe > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on Jane Doe Ledge and finish/topout on John Doe bucket. Maybe FA, idk, crossing lines is fun and worth doing.

Location: Doe > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Unique boulder full of underclings, side pulls, toe hooks, good feet, a challenging arete and good finish. Cool find.The beginning sequence feels weird until its sequenced--there are many ways to start the problem. (Knee bar, heel-toe cam left, heel-toe cam right).Start with a left hand sidepull and a right hand undercling triangle pinch. Climb up the face using edges, good feet and the arete.

Location: Amoeba > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the obvious jugs down low. Climb up the shallow dihedral using small crimps. Pull yourself up over the rounded topout.

Location: Pod > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start somewhat low in the crack on a really good sidepull. Follow the crack up and left to a good hold and then dyno for the top. The left arete is off.A SDS to this line has been done, but the holds down low are somewhat pliable and are ready to explode!

Location: Steamed Buns > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS right line on the boulder.

Location: Steamed Buns > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Left side of the boulder.

Location: Steamed Buns > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Stand start on two opposing side pulls. Climb the face right of the low angle crack. The rock left of the crack is off.

Location: Stolen Goods > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start compressed on a small left hand crimp and a right hand edge. pull onto the steep boulder using the big right foot. Make a big move to a right hand edge and bust to the crack out left. Climb left following the crack until you can top out. The rock quality and climbing on this boulder is first rate!

Location: Summit Pile > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the tall face on crimps.

Location: Frumpy > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start compressed with left hand on jug undercling/sidepull and right hand on any sloper. Pull onto the floating arete and climb it to the top. Be mindful of the chossy jug near the top.

Location: Wavy Flakes > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start just below the prow overhang matched on the large sloping edge. Slap up left to an edge and throw right to dish. Finish up the bulge

Location: Wavy Flakes > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start with a broken edge crimp. Climb straight up using good side pulls, under-clings, and a large left hand block. Finish with a jug ledge.

Location: Wavy Flakes > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start all the way under the overhang with left hand on a gentle seam and right hand on an undercling bump. Throw for the starting ledge/finish for Fudge Muggler.

Location: Noel > North Mountain > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A somewhat newer addition to North Mountain.Start matched low on the right side with a large broken shelf and climb left through a pair of small crimps, great slopers and compression. Exit up and left of the prow.Don't let your goonie legs dab on the slab below!

Location: James Brown Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the overhanging arete in the pit. Make a huge throw to a slopey rail.

Location: James Brown Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Another powerful compression line. This one might definitely be height dependent as you'll need every possible inch to span this boulder.SDS squeezing the prow and work your way up the left and right arete until its possible to mantle over the top.

Location: James Brown Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Like many of the classic lines at Haycock, this is all about compression.SDS on obvious, yet low, jug. Dyno up to slopers on the faint lip and then trend leftwards. Climb up the prow and then trend back right slightly towards the topout finish.

Location: The Big Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Slabby jug haul. Follow the prominent crack up the slab. Careful as the landing has a bad ramp that would surely ruin an ankle or two!

Location: The Big Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climb the big zig zagging crack system

Location: The Big Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Its a shame this line doesnt get more traffic. This is a great v4 with some very interesting and crimpy moves.Find the vertical seam of the south facing face (see topo picture). Start with a high diagonal crimp and climb up on crimpy sidepulls. Find the faint gully like feature of the rock that appears when the sidepulls run out. High step up and press up onto the top section of the boulder.

Location: The Big Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Where to begin with this one! This climb has a somewhat sordid history. For an informative description of the many versions of Mangler, be sure to check out the entry in the paper guidebook.Climb down into the small pit and start on both sides of the block. Climb up and out of the pit.

Location: The Big Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Find the massive wave like boulder just near the Mangler. Starting on nice crimps in the middle of this boulder, climb up and right towards the off-width that is formed by the adjacent boulder. Enter into the off-width and finish it up!

Location: The Big Area > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start at the bottom of the pit with a RH sloper and a LH gaston on a good crimp. Make a few easy moves, then enter the crux by reaching out to a horrible LH crimp and continuing up to the lip via a bad right hand pinch. After hitting the lip, climb up the relatively easy slab to the top of the boulder.

Location: River of Rocks > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the starting holds of Amber. With the use of a foot out left, mantle the starting holds. Once your standing on top of the beginning of the Amber rail, head up and left to a large, left facing jug. Climb the slab to the top of the boulder.

Location: River of Rocks > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS under the base of the finger crack. Do a move to gain the crack and climb it to it's end where a mantle encounter awaits on cool holds and awesome rock.

Location: River of Rocks > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Are you looking for a roof problem at Haycock?! If so, then this is the line you'll want to check out. Interesting moves lead you out this cave. If you refrain from researching the beta, you'll have a fun time trying to decipher the odd yet fun moves that will lead you to higher ground!Start in the back of the cave on a flake and work your way towards the prominent notch. Figure out how to get around the lip and up through the little chasm. Hit the final seam and revel in the fact that you just did some acrobatic moves to get there!The easiest way to get to this problem is by coming from the Caves. Once you hit the caves, go around the backside and scramble up along the talus. Under My Thumb is about 150 yards uphill. Its somewhat hard to spot.

Location: The Snail Boulder > Mothership Connection > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start with a bad left hand side pull and the high, sharp, right hand side pull. Pull onto the boulder and do a big move up and left to the jug lip. Climb the jiggy lip as it turns more vertical and climb to the cool apex of the boulder.

Location: The Snail Boulder > Mothership Connection > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with left hand on a bad sloping side pull in the roof and right hand low on the sloping arete. Pull on and compress your way up the Snails head. This boulder is pretty cool for being so short and would be even cooler if it wasn't so crowded by other boulders.

Location: The Snail Boulder > Mothership Connection > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Climbers choice of three small crimps in a horizontal seam. Pick your two holds, pull onto the boulder with bad feet and dyno to the top.

Location: Space Ghost > Mothership Connection > Haycock Mountain (Nockamixon) > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start in the back of the cave with a left hand side pull and a right hand side pull. Stem and drop knee your way through the crux, climbing hard right toward the jug on the arete. Once at the jug, climb up the arete on cool holds and top out. **Be mindful of the semi-detached looking jug at the top.

Location: Vital Juices > Livezey Rock > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: The overhanging chimney crack to the right of Vital Juices... is 5.9.

Location: Vital Juices > Livezey Rock > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: The V6 is called Mayday, climbed mid-90's by Colby Barth. climbs the sit, from the far left, follows a seam up and right. (thanks Matt S.)Rated 5.13 and V7 on this route's first ascents on toprope (1980s) and unroped (1999), it now generally rated 5.12/.12+ and V5+/V6-.

Location: Main Rock > Livezey Rock > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Eliminate traverse problem, trending uphill, with surprisingly consistent little crimps and interesting footwork. Start on the uphill portion of Livezey rock, just right of the crack/flake system for the rightmost toprope climb. Crack/flake is off, for full effect on the start. Move vertically a few moves (but not to the top of the face) then traverse right until the rock ends in the hillside. Recommend 2 crash pads, not because of the height but because there's a big log and a rock in the landing that you need to protect.

Location: Main Rock > Livezey Rock > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: It starts directly in front of the man hole, the same place as the nine but break left. Climb through the small roof and go up the face. Stay well right of the arete. There are some small horizontals and side pulls up the bulge. I think it's on the harder side of 5.11 - a solid V3 boulder problem.

Location: Middle Boulder > Livezey Rock > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Begin as far out to the right as you can on the overhang. Traverse left until you get to the jugs at the far left and top out.Beta Vid

Location: The Funky  Slab > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Walk up the slabby right-hand face of the boulder. Easy, a good place for new outdoor boulderers to build confidence and practice footwork.

Location: The Funky  Slab > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on a left sidepull and right sloper. Traverse left with an undercling and make a reachy move to a prominent sidepull jug. Move up and left on slopers to a solid top out.Beta Vid

Location: The Funky  Slab > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start standing with a left hand side pull and a bad right hand sloper. Climb the slab up and slightly to the left. The footwork is important.

Location: The Funky  Slab > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Stand start with left hand on a crimp at head height and right hand on a low undercling around waist height. Smear feet and climb up. Traditionally the undercling rails used on The Squeaky Hinge are off.

Location: The Funky  Slab > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the jug and feet out right. Goes straight up on bad slopers. Gets slick in the sun, plan accordingly.

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start matched on a jug to the right of the prominent crack in the middle of the face. Move left and climb the crack/flake. A bushy top out is possible, watch for poison ivy.Beta Vid

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the far right near the remains of wheatpased sign a LARPer put up to warn of the overwhelming strength of his spells (this is actually what the sign said before it faded...). Traverse left along the dihedral until you reach the left arÃªte. Climb up until you're done, a bushwhacking top out is possible but not that fun.

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on far right corner and traverse across the dihedral to the arete, staying low. Head around the corner and make a reachy move to a small left crimp. Move up the crimpy face. Topping out is possible but not that fun. Basically Gem of a Stem plus the left side of the Mixed Up arÃªte.

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on "Gem of a Stem," but stay high then turn the corner to make a dynamic move with the left hand to a good jug and continue to traverse high, finishing on a high jug (the meat hook as it's sometimes known).instagram.com/p/CQiyyUCjgeh/

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: âStart on huge jugs at the bottom left of the hole. Move left through broken holds, then up and right to jugs. This was a 4 star problem, but many holds have broken over the years. It was much easier but much more interesting.â

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: One of the best moderate boulders in the park, with great holds and fun movement on an obvious feature. Sit start with your hands matched on the perfect edges at the bottom of the overhanging corner, and open with a powerful blind throw left to the sloping edge. Follow obvious holds up the arete and into the mail slot, and quest up over the lip on good holds until you hit a two-handed finishing jug about two feet above the lip. I dropped down from here as the problems in this area don't top out, but you probably could top out and make things difficult for yourself if you want to prove a point.As of September 2020 there was zero chalk on anything above the mail slot, but the holds are all there, you just need to do a little looking. Get on this thing, it's amazing!

Route: Two Czech Bros Get Out Torqued
Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the undercling start of "Two Czechoslovakian Brothers"(to the right of torque). Then go left from the jug to the dyno holds of "Torque" and dyno to the top.Beta Video:instagram.com/tv/CWOGYJ6DsEâ¦(*Top is very SHARP*)

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start matched in the low crimp rail. Use Â a Gaston and some fancy hips and make the move to a geometric hold. Finish on the upper section of breaking my heart,Â avoiding the arete cave feature.

Location: Torque Boulder (aka the Precious?) > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A classic 3 move power boulder, if only it wasn't an eliminate!Start as per torque, make a long move to the mail slot directly from the start, skipping all other intermediates. Match the mail slot reset feet and dyno to the torque finish.Those under 5' 10" need not apply.

Location: Forbidden Boulder > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Hop on either end of the boulder with the Battle of Germantown memorial plaque on it. Traverse the path of least resistance for an introductory V0ish route. Take other lines or eliminate holds for more tougher problems, or to avoid seeping mud and moss in spots. You'll get similar reactions as on the Kelly Drive Boulder since it sees a bit of foot and bike traffic.

Location: Forbidden Boulder > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: SDS with opposing sidepulls. Grab a pinch and move up and right along jugs to the same finish as Forbidden Traverse.

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the prominent jug farthest to the right. Move up and left on jugs to reach a long shelf. It's a real choose your own adventure kinda thing here, plenty to choose from. Continue traversing left to the same finish as The Rainbow for a V2.Beta Vid

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start matched on the prominent jug in the middle of the face. Follow the flake up to the right using only the holds along that seam. The shelf at the top is the finish. If you really have something to prove you could probably top it out for a V2 :)

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start matched on the horn on the far right. Traverse left along the lip as far as possible then top out. The rock on the bottom left is off.Beta Vid

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start on the big chalked-up ledge and make a big move up to a good hold. Ride the rail rightwards, crossing into the finish of The Rainbow.

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: A fun arete sit starting on the slab, climbing the water streak.

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Sit start at the beginning of the crack system and bust a move up to the prominent jug ledge above the end of the crack. Keep following the good holds into the finish of The Rainbow.

Location: The Danger Dam > Wissahickon Valley Park > Philly > Southeastern Lowlands > Pennsylvania
Description: Start at the bottom of the crack and make a move or two up it. With your right hand established somewhere amongst the very chalked bulge where the crack splits, get yourself set up for a big throw left to the massive left-facing flake.
